# Real, live, PII-bearing roster data synced from Duke OneDrive. As of
# 2026-07, real_schedule/ reads (never writes) these files at runtime for
# the swap/clinic-coverage checking tools — a deliberate, explicit decision
# by the chief resident. They must still never enter version control.
# Two patterns: the plain OneDrive sync creates a real directory here, but
# a symlink named the same (e.g. a convenience symlink into a worktree
# during development) is a different filesystem type and the trailing-slash
# form alone does NOT match it — both forms are listed so nothing named
# Resident_Schedules, of either kind, can ever be accidentally staged.
Resident_Schedules/
Resident_Schedules

# Real chief-resident passphrase — never commit. See secrets.toml.example.
.streamlit/secrets.toml

# Program Policies
ProgramPolicies/

# Real, PII-bearing resident roster (names, phone, email, squad/team
# assignments) — same "never enter version control" rule as
# Resident_Schedules/ above.
residents/
